"""
TwoTower-Sovereign — P2 XL: the DECISIVE scaled test of the pure-SSM-context bet, on
HONEST real-text corpus targets.

The N=251 scaled run (train_p2_scaled.py) proved STAGE-1 signal (context->continuation
4.38x chance, strengthening with scale) but STAGE-2 was data-starved (34.6M denoiser on
201 prompts: held-out real 9.2% ~= shuffled 9.8%). This run SCALES UP decisively AND
switches to an honest, cheaper target:

KEY CHANGE — REAL-TEXT CORPUS TARGETS (not mamba's greedy self-continuation):
  * Assemble THOUSANDS of prompts from the repo's own prose (docs/**, READMEs). For each
    text window: prompt = first PROMPT_LEN tokens, target = the NEXT K=8 REAL corpus
    tokens (the honest continuation). Tokenized with the SAME gpt-neox/pythia BPE the
    mamba-2.8b canary uses (vocab 50280). This tests the honest question (does the frozen
    SSM context help predict REAL text) AND makes extraction ~1 canary call per prompt
    (ONE context forward, NO K-step greedy generation) — ~10x faster.
  * Extract the frozen mamba context per prompt from the mctx canary (/debug/forward
    return_context=true). PARALLELIZED (many workers), cached INCREMENTALLY + RESUMABLY to
    a compact b16/base64 JSONL so a mid-run failure loses nothing.

STAGE 1 — kernel/1-NN dual probe (n<<d, NOT a d-dim ridge): context->target-block
  agreement vs chance. Per-position + content-token block-agreement ratio. The
  information floor on the honest real-text task. (Reuses train_p2_scaled's probes.)

STAGE 2 — the decisive scaled denoiser (d_model=1024, 6 layers, 8 heads ~ 116M, the P1
  spec) + a proper 90/10 held-out split. Train THREE conditions on the SAME targets:
  (i) REAL context, (ii) ZERO context, (iii) SHUFFLED context (real vectors, wrong
  prompts). Weight decay + early-stop on held-out. The buleyean complement-KL +
  rejection-contrast loss + the E8-lattice/gate rejection ledger are UNCHANGED.
  DECISIVE metric = HELD-OUT (unseen prompts) real vs zero vs shuffled block-agreement +
  a McNemar paired significance test (n held-out is now large enough for a real p-value).

Run:  python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_xl.py                 # offline, cached
      python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_xl.py --extract        # (re)build dataset
      python3 open-source/gnosis/twotower/train_p2_xl.py --extract-only    # build cache, no train
"""

